article.headline: Wright State 63, Marist 53
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- DaShaun Wood scored 17 points and had seven rebounds to lead Wright State to a 63-53 win over Marist Tuesday night. Vaughn Duggins added 16 points and Todd Brown scored 11 for Wright State (4-5). Wright State had pulled to a 13-point lead, its largest of the game, with 1:03 left in the half and was ahead 28-16 at the break. Marist (8-3) was up by 3 points with 18 minutes left in the first period but never held the lead again. Leading Marist in scoring were Ryan Stilphen with 20 and Will Whittington with 10. Marist shot 39 percent to Wright State's 37 percent, but Wright state was ahead on 3 pointers, with 8 of 20 to Marist's 5 of 19, and free throws, with 17 of 21 to Marist's 10 of 19.
